;Copyright: Reforming laws for our digital reality
Ruch'ojib'al b'anel: Tajin yek'ex taqanem taq tzij richin ri qak'aslem kemtz'ib' wakami


;We should all be able to share, reuse and reinterpret the creativity that inspires us on the Internet.
Qonojel k'o chi yojtikïr yojkomonin, yojokisan chik chuqa yojna'ojin pa ruwi' ri na'onïk nuyäk qak'u'x chi rij ri K'amaya'l.


;Intellectual Property (IP) rights were designed as a practical solution to advance creativity in all its forms: arts, science, business, and technology. In order for IP to continue sowing seeds for the future of the Web, our laws need to support the speed and spirit of collaboration that defines our digital world.
Ri taq ruch'ojib'al Ichinil Na'owinïk (IP) xewachib'ëx achi'el jun samajel soloj richin nichilabëx ri na'owinïk pa ronojel rub'eyal: taq na'ojinïk, etamab'alil, loq'k'ayij chuqa' na'ob'äl. Richin chi ri IP tusamajib'ej ri ruk'aslem Ajk'amaya'l ri chwa'q kab'ij, ri taqanem taq qatzij nikajo' chi tikito' ri aninäq chuqa' ri nuyäk qak'u'x richin yojto'on, ri nikiq'alajisaj qa ruwach'ulew.


